issue.title: Add MISSION.md references to feature specification files
issue.body:
Problem:
Currently, none of our feature spec files under features/ explicitly reference the project mission (MISSION.md). The `--validate-features` command relies on finding the string “MISSION.md” in each spec file and will fail until we add those references.

Goal:
- Ensure every Markdown file in the `features/` directory contains at least one reference to `MISSION.md`, so that `npm run validate:features` (or `node src/lib/main.js --validate-features`) exits cleanly.

Implementation Steps:
1. In each file under `features/` (e.g. `BATCH_MODE.md`, `PERFORMANCE_BENCHMARK.md`, `PI_SERVER.md`, `HIGH_PRECISION_ALGORITHMS.md`, `ERROR_TOLERANCE.md`, `CONVERGENCE_CHART.md`):
   - Immediately below the top-level title (e.g. `# Batch Calculation`), insert a line such as:
     ```md
     _See the project mission in [MISSION.md](../MISSION.md) to understand the scope and context of this feature._
     ```
2. Run `npm run validate:features` to verify that all specs now pass the mission-reference check (exit code 0).
3. No changes to source code or tests are required; this is purely a documentation update.

Verification:
- After updating, run:
  ```bash
  npm run validate:features
  ```
  and confirm the console outputs:
  ```
  All features reference MISSION.md
  ```
  and exits with code 0.

No new files should be created or deleted. Only the existing `features/*.md` files should be modified to include the mission link.
